column1: The matrix uses following top level privileges:

column5: - authority to make decision about resource configuration
- permission to use the resource on control plane level. Does not cover TCP level exposed by the resource itself i.e. does not cover data plane permissions.
- permission to tune resource on control plane level. Does not cover software level tunnelables exposed by the resource itself i.e. does not cover data plane tunning permissions.
- permission to decommission resource on a control plane level. Does not cover data plane permissions related to protecting data kept by software behind there resource
- permission to inspect state of the resource at control plane level. Does not cover access to business data handled by the resource.
- full permission to the resource and inner resources incl. delete. Should be used only by break glass roles.
